  "body": "Issue\r\n\r\nI addressed the same error in another issue but I now need this to work in rinkeby (the only public testnet I can get to sync so far)\r\n\r\nUnable to get a truffle console when sync to Rinkeby testnet\r\n\r\nSteps to Reproduce:\r\nIn one Powershell instance run geth:\r\ngeth --networkid=4 --datadir=$HOME/.rinkeby --syncmode=\"light\" --rpc --rpcapi \"db,eth,net,web3,personal\" --cache=1024  --rpcport 8545 --rpcaddr \"127.0.0.1\" --rpccorsdomain \"*\"--ethstats='yournode:Respect my authoritah!@stats.rinkeby.io' --bootnodes=enode://a24ac7c5484ef4ed0c5eb2d36620ba4e4aa13b8c84684e1b4aab0cebea2ae45cb4d375b77eab56516d34bfbd3c1a833fc51296ff084b770b94fb9028c4d25ccf@52.169.42.101:30303?discport=30304\r\n\r\nIn another Powershell instance:\r\ntype ' truffle console --network rinkeby' in the truffle project directory\r\n\r\nExpected Behavior:\r\n\r\nI get a truffle console:\r\n\r\n    truffle(rinkeby):\r\n\r\nActual Results\r\n\r\nPS C:\\Users<dir>\\Ethereum Projects\\truffleprojects\\FullStackVoting> truffle console --network rinkeby\r\n\r\nevents.js:163\r\n      throw er; // Unhandled 'error' event\r\n      ^\r\nError: Invalid JSON RPC response: \"<!DOCTYPE html>\\n<html lang etc...\r\ntitle>\\n</head>\\n<body>\\n<pre>Cannot POST /</pre>\\n</body>\\n\"etc....\r\n\r\nEnvironment\r\n\r\n    Operating System: Win 10 32 bit\r\n    Truffle version: v3.2.1\r\n    Ethereum client: Geth 1.6.1-unstable\r\n    node version: v7.9.0\r\n    npm version: 4.6.1\r\n\r\nThanks for any assistance ...",
